properties.description: Posted by BuderimChambers Island is set in the Maroochy River. A footbridge connects it to the river bank. A great spot for afternoons in the sun, fishing, playing with the kids. Picnic areas and toilets are on the island.

properties.name: Alexandra Headland
properties.description: Posted by Buderim167 Alexandra Parade, Maroochydore,AustraliaAlex is a great beach, safe for the kids, patrolled and a coupla good little surf breaks as well!

properties.name: Australia Zoo
properties.description: Posted by BuderimThe famous home of the late and great legend, Steve Irwin, Crocodile Hunter and animal lover extraordinaire. This place is amazing and a must see destination if you come to the coast.

properties.name: Buderim Forest Walk
properties.description: Posted by Buderim Harrys Lane, Buderim, AustraliaThis is probably the most beautiful spot around Buderim. Read more at Buderim Forest page on Buderim\'s website

properties.name: Buderim Historical Tramway Walking Track
properties.description: Posted by BuderimThis is an untouched area where the old train ran from Palwoods to Buderim in the early 1900\'s. Get more info from the website link

properties.name: Foote Sanctuary
properties.description: Posted by BuderimPark Street, Buderim,AustraliaThe Foote Sanctuary is a very large tract of land given to the community in memory of Eric Foote, killed in World War One.

properties.description: Posted by Buderim Kondalilla Falls Road, Queensland, AustraliaFollow this road to an amazing swimming area with spectacular views of the Blackall Range. Tracks that go into the wilderness are perfect for hikers, loads of wildlife. Just another wonderful spot on the Sunshine Coast

properties.description: Posted by BuderimQuarry Road, Coolum, Queensland, AustraliaAn interesting vesige of an ancient volcano, Mount Coolum rises at the edge of the pacific ocean, overlooking a beautiful beach and golf course. Worth the climb, but only if you are fit!.
